---

<BaseLayout
  title="Elliott Wave Theory Guide 2026: Master Wave Analysis"
  description="Learn Elliott Wave Theory for forex trading. Understand impulse and corrective waves, trading rules, and how to apply wave analysis to real markets."
>
  <!-- BREADCRUMB -->
  <Breadcrumb slot="breadcrumb" items={[
    { text: 'Home', href: '/' },
    { text: 'Guides', href: '/guides/' },
    { text: 'Elliott Wave', current: true }
  ]} />

  <!-- HERO SECTION -->
  <section class="hero-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <div class="hero-badge">
          <span class="badge-icon">üåä</span>
          TECHNICAL ANALYSIS
        </div>
        <h1 class="hero-title">Elliott Wave Theory</h1>
        <p class="hero-description">
          Understand market structure through wave patterns. Learn the 5-3 wave pattern that governs all financial markets.
        </p>

        <!-- Key Stats -->
        <div class="stats-grid">
          {keyStats.map((stat) => (
            <div class="stat-card">
              <div class="stat-icon">{stat.icon}</div>
              <span class="stat-value">{stat.value}</span>
              <span class="stat-label">{stat.label}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ANCHOR NAVIGATION -->
  <nav class="anchor-nav" id="anchorNav">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="anchor-links">
        {anchorMenuItems.map((item) => (
          <a href={item.href} class="anchor-link">{item.text}</a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- OVERVIEW -->
  <section class="section" id="overview">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="section-title">What is Elliott Wave Theory?</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          A method of technical analysis that identifies repeating wave patterns in price charts, discovered by Ralph Nelson Elliott in the 1930s.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="intro-content">
        <p>Elliott observed that market prices move in predictable patterns he called "waves." These waves reflect the collective psychology of market participants - optimism and pessimism, fear and greed.</p>
        <p>The basic structure consists of 5 waves in the direction of the main trend (impulse waves), followed by 3 waves against it (corrective waves). This 5-3 pattern repeats at every scale, from minute charts to multi-decade cycles.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="wave-structure">
        <div class="wave-diagram">
          <h3>The Basic Pattern</h3>
          <div class="diagram-content">
            <pre>
        5
       /\
      /  \   B
     /    \ /\
    3      X  \
   /\     A    C
  /  \
 /    4
1
 \   /
  \ /
   2
            </pre>
          </div>
          <p class="diagram-caption">5 impulse waves (1-2-3-4-5) followed by 3 corrective waves (A-B-C)</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- IMPULSE WAVES -->
  <section class="section section-alt" id="impulse">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="section-title">The 5 Impulse Waves</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Impulse waves move in the direction of the main trend. Waves 1, 3, and 5 are motive (trending), while 2 and 4 are corrective (counter-trend).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="waves-list">
        {impulseWaves.map((wave, index) => (
          <div class="wave-card impulse">
            <div class="wave-number">{index + 1}</div>
            <div class="wave-content">
              <h3 class="wave-title">{wave.wave}</h3>
              <p class="wave-description">{wave.description}</p>
              <div class="wave-characteristics">
                <strong>Key characteristics:</strong>
                <ul>
                  {wave.characteristics.map((char) => (
                    <li>{char}</li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CORRECTIVE WAVES -->
  <section class="section" id="corrective">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="section-title">The 3 Corrective Waves</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          After the 5-wave impulse, a 3-wave correction follows. These waves move against the main trend and are labeled A, B, C.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="waves-list">
        {correctiveWaves.map((wave) => (
          <div class="wave-card corrective">
            <div class="wave-letter">{wave.wave.split(' ')[1]}</div>
            <div class="wave-content">
              <h3 class="wave-title">{wave.wave}</h3>
              <p class="wave-description">{wave.description}</p>
              <div class="wave-characteristics">
                <strong>Key characteristics:</strong>
                <ul>
                  {wave.characteristics.map((char) => (
                    <li>{char}</li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- Fibonacci Table -->
      <div class="fibo-section">
        <h3>Fibonacci Relationships</h3>
        <p>Elliott waves are closely tied to Fibonacci ratios. Use these relationships to project wave targets and validate counts.</p>
        <div class="fibo-table-wrapper">
          <table class="fibo-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Wave</th>
                <th>Typical Relationship</th>
                <th>Note</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {fiboRelationships.map((fibo) => (
                <tr>
                  <td class="fibo-wave">{fibo.relationship}</td>
                  <td>{fibo.typical}</td>
                  <td class="fibo-note">{fibo.note}</td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RULES AND GUIDELINES -->
  <section class="section section-alt" id="rules">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="section-title">Rules & Guidelines</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Elliott Wave has three unbreakable rules and several guidelines. Breaking a rule means your wave count is wrong.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rules-section">
        <h3>The 3 Unbreakable Rules</h3>
        <div class="rules-grid">
          {rules.map((rule, index) => (
            <div class="rule-card">
              <span class="rule-badge">Rule {index + 1}</span>
              <h4 class="rule-title">{rule.title}</h4>
              <p class="rule-description">{rule.description}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="guidelines-section">
        <h3>Guidelines (Not Rules)</h3>
        <div class="guidelines-grid">
          {guidelines.map((guideline) => (
            <div class="guideline-card">
              <h4 class="guideline-title">{guideline.title}</h4>
              <p class="guideline-description">{guideline.description}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TRADING APPLICATIONS -->
  <section class="section" id="trading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="section-title">Trading with Elliott Wave</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Practical applications of wave theory for real trading decisions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="applications-grid">
        {tradingApplications.map((app) => (
          <div class="application-card">
            <span class="app-icon">{app.icon}</span>
            <h3 class="app-title">{app.title}</h3>
            <p class="app-description">{app.description}</p>
            <div class="app-example">
              <strong>Example:</strong> {app.example}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="trading-tip">
        <p><strong>Pro tip:</strong> Don't trade Wave 1 or Wave A - too uncertain. Focus on Wave 3 entries (highest probability) and Wave 5 (end of trend). Always confirm with price action and other indicators.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BROKERS SECTION -->
  <section class="section section-alt" id="brokers">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="section-title">Best Brokers for Technical Analysis</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Brokers with advanced charting tools for wave analysis.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="brokers-grid">
        {featuredBrokers.map((broker) => (
          <div class={`broker-card ${broker.featured ? 'featured' : ''}`}>
            {broker.featured && <span class="featured-badge">Top Pick</span>}
            <div class="broker-header">
              <img src={broker.logo} alt={`${broker.name} logo`} class="broker-logo" loading="lazy" />
              <div class="broker-rating">
                <span class="rating-stars">{'‚òÖ'.repeat(parseInt(broker.stars))}</span>
                <span class="rating-value">{broker.rating}/5</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <h3 class="broker-name">{broker.name}</h3>
            <ul class="broker-features">
              {broker.features.map((feature) => (
                <li>{feature}</li>
              ))}
            </ul>
            <a href={broker.ctaLink} class="broker-cta">{broker.ctaText}</a>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="section-cta">
        <a href="/brokers" class="cta-button secondary">
          Compare All Brokers
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
  <section class="section" id="faqs">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="section-title">Elliott Wave FAQs</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Common questions about wave analysis.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-list">
        {faqs.map((faq) => (
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">{faq.question}</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">{faq.answer}</p>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FINAL CTA -->
  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="final-cta">
        <h2>Ready to Apply Elliott Wave?</h2>
        <p>Practice identifying waves on historical charts first. Then test your analysis with a demo account before risking real money.</p>
        <div class="cta-buttons">
          <a href="/brokers" class="cta-button primary">Find a Broker</a>
          <a href="/guides/forex-strategy" class="cta-button secondary">More Strategies</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

